Title: Two-dimensional QCD and instanton contribution
Authors: A. Bassetto, L. Griguolo and F. Vian
Comments: 11 pages, Revtex, amssymb. Talk given by F. Vian at the XVII Autumn
  School "QCD: Perturbative or Nonperturbative?", Lisbon (Portugal), September
  29 - October 4, 1999. To appear in the proceedings
Report-no: DFPD 99/TH 49; UPRF-99-18
\\
  In these notes Yang-Mills theories in 1+1 dimensions are reviewed. Instantons
on a sphere prove to be -in the decompactification limit- the key issue to
clarify an old controversy between equal-time and light-front quantization.
